net.akami.mask.alteration

Interface CalculationCanceller<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CalculationAlteration<T>, java.lang.Comparable<CalculationAlteration>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CalculationCache

    public interface CalculationCanceller<T>
extends CalculationAlteration<T>
    The CalculationCanceller class is one of the two core object of the alteration system, provided by the API. A Canceller checks, as every alteration, if it can have an impact on a certain expression. If yes, then it cancels the scheduled calculation, and gives a merge that might be different or not than if the calculation was computed.

    For instance, the CalculationCache checks whether the expression has already been evaluated, and gives the merge stored if it is the case.

      • resultIfCancelled

        T resultIfCancelled(T... input)
        Defines what merge must be returned instead of the initial calculation.

        Note that no validity check must be done inside the method itself, since the #appliesTo(T...) method should already take care of that.
        Parameters:
        input - the given input. Depending on the calculation, the getElementsSize of the array might change.
        Returns:
        a merge that might be different or not than the merge that would have been computed without the intervention of the canceller.
